Daud Olatunji, Abeokuta Four persons have died while six others sustained injuries in three separate accidents on Friday along the Abeokuta-Sagamu and the Lagos-Ibadan Expressways. The Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps, Ogun State Command, Clement Oladele, disclosed this in a statement on Saturday. READ ALSO: 268 Nigerians arrive in Abuja from China He said, “The remains of the victims have been deposited at the Idera hospital morgue while the survivors are receiving medical attention.’’ Oladele advised motorists to drive cautiously and desist from driving against traffic to avoid loss of lives.